Package com.irurueta.navigation.inertial.calibration

Class IMUNoiseEstimator

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.irurueta.navigation.inertial.calibration.IMUNoiseEstimator
  • public class IMUNoiseEstimator
extends java.lang.Object
    This class estimates IMU accelerometer and gyroscope noise variances and PSD's (Power Spectral Densities) along with their average values. This estimator must be used when the body where the IMU is attached remains static on the same position with zero velocity while capturing data. To compute PSD's, this estimator assumes that IMU samples are obtained at a constant provided rate equal to getTimeInterval() seconds. If not available, IMU sampling rate average can be estimated using IMUTimeIntervalEstimator. This estimator does NOT require the knowledge of current location and body orientation. This estimator is very similar to IMUBiasEstimator except that location and orientation is not required, hence noise levels can be correctly determined, but average levels do not necessarily math IMU bias values.

      • addBodyKinematics

        public boolean addBodyKinematics​(BodyKinematics kinematics)
                          throws LockedException
        Adds a sample of body kinematics (accelerometer + gyroscope readings) obtained from an IMU. If estimator is already finished, provided sample will be ignored.
        Parameters:
        kinematics - kinematics instance to be added and processed.
        Returns:
        true if provided kinematics instance has been processed, false if it has been ignored.
        Throws:
        LockedException - if estimator is currently running.
